            <a name="usage"/>
            <subsection name="Usage">
                <ol type="1">
                    <li>Unzip
                        <tt>jpbc-1.0.0.zip</tt>
                        to the directory you wish to unzip jPBC 1.0.0.
                    </li>
                    <li>To use jPBC add to your classpath
                        <ol type="1">
                            <li>
                                <tt>jpbc_1.0.0-api.jar</tt>
                                and
                            </li>

                            <li><tt>jpbc_1.0.0-plaf.jar</tt>.
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                        To use the wrapper include also
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                <tt>jpbc_1.0.0-pbc.jar</tt>
                                and
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <tt>jna-3.1.0.jar</tt>.
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                        Rememeber that for using the wrappen you must compile a shared library
                        which links jPBC with PBC. Go
                        <a href="./docs/pbcwrapper.html">here</a>
                        to see how to do that.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                <p>
                    You will find these dependencies into the jars folder.
                </p>
